title: S.J. boys: Washington Twp. moves on in Coaches Tournament
text:
Nonleague. Tim Birney scored the lone goal to give Shawnee the 1-0 victory over visiting Hammonton. Luke Morgan assisted in the 39th minute.
Mainland defeated visiting Williamstown, 1-0, in double overtime on an own goal. Matt Stelletano had eight saves. 
Ty Pawling and Andrew Tomaino scored to give visiting Ocean City a 2-0 win over Delsea. Matt Brook had an assist. 
Jake Rutledge scored twice to give host Cape May Tech a 2-0 victory over GCIT. Robert Edmunds made eight saves. Boys' Cross-Country Owen Long of Haddon Township finished first in the Varsity Boys A Race at the NYC Cross-Country Carnival at Van Cortland Park. Long completed the 4,000-meter course in 12 minutes, 57 seconds.
Haddonfield runners Austin Stoner, Greg Pelose, Colin Gallagher, and Derek Gess placed second through fifth to lead the Bulldawgs to the team victory. Girls' Soccer Emily Gray and Deanna Balsama scored to give fourth-seeded Washington Township a 2-0 win over visiting 13th seed Hammonton in the first round of the Coaches Tournament.
In other tournament action, Shaye McGoey scored twice in fifth-seeded Cherokee's 3-0 win over visiting 12th-seeded Rancocas Valley. Tori Hampton also had a goal. Field Hockey Katie Miller's first-half goal was all Camden Catholic needed in a 1-0 win over Paul VI 1-0 in Olympic Conference play at home. Kelli Connolly assisted.
Nonleague. Allie Trimble scored in the second half to give Williamstown a 1-0 win over visiting Vineland. Michelle Teodoro secured the shutout. 
Allison McCormick had a goal and an assist on the road to help West Deptford defeat Cherokee, 3-0. 
Gab Scocca scored twice to power St. Joseph to a 2-0 win over host Holy Spirit. Julia Jones had an assist. 
Colonial Conference. Julia Bennett and Michelle Creamer each scored twice to lead host Haddonfield to a 7-0 victory against Overbrook. Meghan Smart had two assists.
